# Financial Risk Hedging Percent

## identifier
de13147

## type
float

## definition
This is the ratio, as at the relevant date, of the level of investments that are protected against adverse changes in the market as a portion of total investments. A hedge is a transaction where the purpose of the transaction is to protect against adverse changes in the market.

## syntax
### xbrl
- name=FinancialRisk.Hedging.Percent
- classification=baf/bafot/bafot.02.15
- period=instant
